      </p>

      <div class="prose max-w-none">
        <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">1. Product Quality and Selection</h2>

        <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-4 mb-6">
          <p class="font-semibold text-green-900">The Foundation of Excellence</p>
          <p class="text-green-800">High-quality products are the cornerstone of any great dispensary. Look for dispensaries that prioritize tested, premium cannabis.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-3">What to Look For:</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <li><strong>Lab Testing:</strong> All products should be tested for potency, pesticides, heavy metals, and contaminants. Certificates of Analysis (COAs) should be readily available.</li>
          <li><strong>Variety:</strong> Great dispensaries offer diverse strains (indica, sativa, hybrid), multiple product types (flower, edibles, concentrates, topicals), and various potency levels.</li>
          <li><strong>Freshness:</strong> Products should be properly stored and rotated. Flower should be fresh, aromatic, and properly cured.</li>
          <li><strong>Premium Brands:</strong> Top dispensaries carry reputable brands known for quality and consistency.</li>
          <li><strong>Organic Options:</strong> Look for organically grown cannabis without harmful chemicals.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">2. Knowledgeable and Friendly Staff</h2>

